Show HN: Code to Prompt (Chat-GPT)
text:
I have implemented a small Go program that reads files in a directory and compiles their data into an output file or prints the results on the terminal. This program may be quite useful for people who are tired of copying and pasting individual files in ChatGPT in order to ask questions about their content.

Please take a look and share your feedback =]

Show HN: Quivr – Crowdsourced Dating
text:
We just launched Quivr about a week ago. The idea is that the public votes on matches for daters, who have the work done for them. Our userbase is mostly matchmakers (women) as well as daters.

Looking for suggestions and criticism, as well as early adopters who want to help us build the product into what singles would love using more than standard apps.
